---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Playground"
  description="Future home of the DCL browser playground, editor, compiler diagnostics, IR view, and diagrams."
>
  <section class="content-wrap">
    <article class="prose">
      <h1>Playground</h1>
      <p>
        The DCL playground is planned as an interactive place to write capability
        models, run the compiler in the browser, inspect diagnostics, view
        intermediate representation, and generate diagrams.
      </p>

      <div class="notice">
        <strong>Not implemented yet</strong>
        <p>
          This first website is static and content-first. Monaco editor,
          compiler WASM, diagnostics, IR views, Cytoscape diagrams, and runtime
          execution are future capabilities.
        </p>
      </div>

      <h2>Planned Extension Points</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Editor shell for Monaco or another browser code editor.</li>
        <li>Compiler WASM loading and version selection.</li>
        <li>Diagnostics panel for parser and semantic feedback.</li>
        <li>IR view for compiler output and analysis.</li>
        <li>Diagram area for capability, policy, and lifecycle visualization.</li>
      </ul>
    </article>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
